  "source_id": "stroke",
  "name": "Stroke - Comprehensive Provider Query (Multi-Resource)",
  "description": "Provider-level query identifying all stroke patients via Condition (stroke dx) + MedicationRequest (alteplase or antiplatelets). Path C captures patients on antiplatelets without coded stroke dx (primary prevention or undocumented TIA).",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete stroke patient population for a stroke quality initiative. Some patients have a coded cerebral infarction or CVA diagnosis. Others are on aspirin or clopidogrel without a formal stroke diagnosis — typically primary cardiovascular prevention or undocumented TIAs. Run multiple FHIR queries — diagnosis and stroke-relevant medications — and union the patient sets.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all my stroke patients.",
    "broad": "Find all stroke patients — by diagnosis, by alteplase (acute thrombolysis), or by antiplatelet medications. Run multiple queries and union the patient sets.",
    "expert": "Run two queries. (1) Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|432504007,http://snomed.info/sct|230690007 — stroke/CVA dx. (2) MedicationRequest?code=http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|8410,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|1191,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|32968 — alteplase + antiplatelets. Union the patient IDs."
  },
